<https://www.ed.ac.uk/kg/ent/03696a806e1d> a :Role ;
    rdfs:label """PROF
Personal Chair of Physics Education
,
School of Physics and Astronomy
https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0757-9628
Phone
+44 (0)131 650 6716
Email
ross.galloway
ed.ac
uk
Website
http://www.ph.ed.ac.uk/people/ross-galloway
Personal profile
Biography
I am a member of the Edinburgh Physics Education Research group (EdPER) and my research activity is related to the learning and teaching of physics.  I have interests in a wide range of pedagogic research areas, including the development of student problem solving skills, diagnostic testing, Peer Instruction, and flipped classroom pedagogies.
Teaching
I teach on a number of courses, including Physics 1A Foundations, Physics of Fields and Matter, and Introductory Astrophysics.  I also supervise Senior Honours projects, MPhys projects, and Group projects.
Education/Academic qualification
Doctor of Philosophy (PhD), Solar Physics,
University of Glasgow
Award Date: 1 Jan 2006
Master in Science, Astronomy & Physics,
University of Glasgow
Award Date: 1 Jan 2002""" ;
